  "summary": {
    "as": "Reported to Senate without amendment", 
    "date": "2007-10-04", 
    "text": "Fair Contracts for Growers Act of 2007 - Amends federal law provisions concerning arbitration to define \"livestock,\" \"livestock or poultry contract,\" \"livestock or poultry grower,\" and \"poultry.\" Allows the use of arbitration to resolve a controversy as provided for under a livestock or poultry contract only if, after the controversy arises, both parties consent in writing to use arbitration. Directs the arbitrator to provide to the parties to the contract a written explanation of the factual and legal basis for an award."
  }, 
